# Design Documentation Guide

> How to create and update UI/UX design documentation

## When to Create

- Before frontend development begins
- When establishing design system
- When documenting user flows

## Design System Structure

### Foundation (Design Tokens)
Create these first - they're the building blocks:

1. **COLOR.md** - Color palette and semantic tokens
2. **TYPOGRAPHY.md** - Font scales, weights, line heights
3. **SPACING.md** - Space tokens (4px base unit)
4. **RADIUS.md** - Border radius standards
5. **SHADOWS.md** - Elevation system
6. **MOTION.md** - Animation and transition tokens

### Components (UI Specs)
Document after foundation is defined:

1. **BUTTONS.md** - Button variants, states, sizes
2. **FORMS.md** - Input, Select, Textarea, Checkbox, Radio
3. **FEEDBACK.md** - Toast, Modal, Progress, Loading
4. **ACCESSIBILITY.md** - WCAG compliance standards

### User Experience
Document user flows and journeys:

1. **USER_JOURNEYS.md** - User stories and touchpoints
2. **USER_FLOWS.md** - Flow diagrams and decision points
3. **SCENARIOS.md** - Use cases and edge cases

## Quality Standards

### Design Tokens
- ✅ **Semantic naming** (e.g., `--text-default`, not `--gray-900`)
- ✅ **Consistent scales** (e.g., spacing: 4px, 8px, 12px, 16px...)
- ✅ **Accessibility checked** (contrast ratios, touch targets)
- ❌ **No hard-coded values** in components

### Components
- ✅ **All states documented** (default, hover, focus, disabled, error)
- ✅ **Accessibility requirements** (ARIA, keyboard nav)
- ✅ **Responsive behavior** defined
- ✅ **Code examples** provided

### User Flows
- ✅ **Entry and exit points** clear
- ✅ **Decision points** documented
- ✅ **Error states** handled
- ✅ **Edge cases** identified

## Pre-Development Checklist

Before coding ANY UI component:

1. [ ] Read relevant foundation docs (COLOR, TYPOGRAPHY, SPACING)
2. [ ] Read component spec (BUTTONS, FORMS, FEEDBACK)
3. [ ] Check accessibility requirements (ACCESSIBILITY.md)
4. [ ] Verify responsive breakpoints
5. [ ] Use tokens only (no hard-coded values)

## Token Usage Rules

### Rule 1: No Hard-Coded Values
```css
/* ❌ Bad */
.button { padding: 12px 16px; color: #1f2937; background: #3b82f6; }

/* ✅ Good */
.button {
  padding: var(--space-3) var(--space-4);
  color: var(--text-default);
  background: var(--color-primary);
}
```

### Rule 2: Semantic Tokens
```css
/* ❌ Bad */
.error { color: var(--color-red-500); }

/* ✅ Good */
.error { color: var(--text-error); }
```

## Template Locations

- Overview: `framework/guides/design/templates/DESIGN.md.template`
- Foundation: `framework/guides/design/templates/ui/foundation/*.template`
- Components: `framework/guides/design/templates/ui/components/*.template`
- UX: `framework/guides/design/templates/ux/*.template`

